{
  "info": {
    "name": "PAS — Keyword Search API",
    "description": "Two endpoints. (1) Store a search (frontend, JWT). (2) The single scraper 'work' endpoint — the scraper just hits it in a loop with x-scraper-name; the server auto-closes the previous term (by name) and gives the next. No docId/scrapeId, no adsCount. Set baseUrl, token, scraperName before running.",
    "schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json"
  },
  "variable": [
    { "key": "baseUrl", "value": "http://localhost:4000" },
    { "key": "token", "value": "" },
    { "key": "scraperName", "value": "fb-keyword-plugin-01" }
  ],
  "item": [
    {
      "name": "1. Store keyword (all networks)",
      "request": {
        "method": "POST",
        "header": [
          { "key": "Authorization", "value": "Bearer {{token}}" },
          { "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }
        ],
        "url": {
          "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/v1/common/keyword-search",
          "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
          "path": ["api", "v1", "common", "keyword-search"]
        },
        "body": {
          "mode": "raw",
          "raw": "{\n  \"value\": \"Nike\",\n  \"type\": 1,\n  \"network\": \"all\",\n  \"email\": \"me@example.com\"\n}"
        },
        "description": "type: 1=keyword, 2=advertiser, 3=domain. network: a slug, comma list, or 'all'. Requires JWT in {{token}}. Re-run → status 'existing' (no duplicate)."
      }
    },
    {
      "name": "2. Store advertiser (facebook,instagram)",
      "request": {
        "method": "POST",
        "header": [
          { "key": "Authorization", "value": "Bearer {{token}}" },
          { "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }
        ],
        "url": {
          "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/v1/common/keyword-search",
          "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
          "path": ["api", "v1", "common", "keyword-search"]
        },
        "body": {
          "mode": "raw",
          "raw": "{\n  \"value\": \"Adidas\",\n  \"type\": 2,\n  \"network\": \"facebook,instagram\",\n  \"email\": \"me@example.com\"\n}"
        }
      }
    },
    {
      "name": "3. Work: facebook (hit 1 — get first term)",
      "request": {
        "method": "POST",
        "header": [
          { "key": "x-scraper-name", "value": "{{scraperName}}" },
          { "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }
        ],
        "url": {
          "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/v1/common/keyword-search/work",
          "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
          "path": ["api", "v1", "common", "keyword-search", "work"]
        },
        "body": {
          "mode": "raw",
          "raw": "{\n  \"type\": \"keyword\",\n  \"network\": \"facebook\"\n}"
        },
        "description": "First hit: completed=0 (nothing to close yet), returns one keyword in data[]. Each data[] item includes users: [{ id, username, email }] — everyone who searched that term, so you know whose request it is."
      }
    },
    {
      "name": "4. Work: facebook (hit 2+ — auto-close prev, get next)",
      "request": {
        "method": "POST",
        "header": [
          { "key": "x-scraper-name", "value": "{{scraperName}}" },
          { "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }
        ],
        "url": {
          "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/v1/common/keyword-search/work",
          "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
          "path": ["api", "v1", "common", "keyword-search", "work"]
        },
        "body": {
          "mode": "raw",
          "raw": "{\n  \"type\": \"keyword\",\n  \"network\": \"facebook\"\n}"
        },
        "description": "Same body as request 3. The server auto-closes the previous term by x-scraper-name (completed=1) and hands the next. Keep re-sending to loop. To mark the previous as no-ads, add: \"status\": \"no_ads_found\"."
      }
    },
    {
      "name": "5. Work: instagram — per-network independence",
      "request": {
        "method": "POST",
        "header": [
          { "key": "x-scraper-name", "value": "ig-keyword-plugin-01" },
          { "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }
        ],
        "url": {
          "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/v1/common/keyword-search/work",
          "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
          "path": ["api", "v1", "common", "keyword-search", "work"]
        },
        "body": {
          "mode": "raw",
          "raw": "{\n  \"type\": \"keyword\",\n  \"network\": \"instagram\"\n}"
        },
        "description": "Even if facebook already scraped 'Nike' today, instagram still gets it (state is per-network)."
      }
    },
    {
      "name": "6. Work: facebook priority",
      "request": {
        "method": "POST",
        "header": [
          { "key": "x-scraper-name", "value": "{{scraperName}}" },
          { "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }
        ],
        "url": {
          "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/v1/common/keyword-search/work",
          "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
          "path": ["api", "v1", "common", "keyword-search", "work"]
        },
        "body": {
          "mode": "raw",
          "raw": "{\n  \"type\": \"keyword\",\n  \"network\": \"facebook\",\n  \"priority\": true\n}"
        },
        "description": "Same auto-close behaviour, priority mode: only hands out freshly re-searched terms. Empty unless you store again first."
      }
    },
    {
      "name": "7. Work: multi network + type (facebook OR instagram, keyword OR advertiser)",
      "request": {
        "method": "POST",
        "header": [
          { "key": "x-scraper-name", "value": "{{scraperName}}" },
          { "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }
        ],
        "url": {
          "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/v1/common/keyword-search/work",
          "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
          "path": ["api", "v1", "common", "keyword-search", "work"]
        },
        "body": {
          "mode": "raw",
          "raw": "{\n  \"type\": [\"keyword\", \"advertiser\"],\n  \"network\": [\"facebook\", \"instagram\"]\n}"
        },
        "description": "type and network may be arrays (or comma lists). The pool is the union of every type x network pair; each returned value carries its own concrete type+network, so a single value may come from facebook OR instagram and be a keyword OR an advertiser. Add \"priority\": true for the same behaviour in priority mode."
      }
    }
  ]
}
